
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-andrews-dnsop-defeat-frag-attack-00.txt'>
    <title>"Defeating DNS/UDP Fragmentation Attacks", Mark Andrews</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-andrews-dnsop-defeat-frag-attack-00.txt</link>
    <description>It is possible to force a DNS server to fragment its response such that a fragmentation reassembly attack can insert records into the response.  This document uses TSIG with a well known key to defeat such attacks.</description>
    <dc:date>2019-07-02T07:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
